(11, 'ADAS Calibration Services', 'ADAS-Calibration-Services-514x416.png', 'Book Your Service Today', '<div class=\"sd-left\">\r\n    <h1 style=\"color: #2ecc71 ;\">Advanced Driver Assistance Systems</h1>\r\n    <h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">What is ADAS ?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>ADAS (Advanced Driver Assistance Systems) are safety features in vehicles that use sensors, cameras, and other technologies to help drivers avoid accidents. Some common ADAS features include automatic emergency braking, lane departure warning, and adaptive cruise control.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the sensors or cameras get disturbed ADAS systems require calibration to ensure safe operation of the vehicle. <a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: #2ecc71;\" href=\"#\"><strong>Autoworld Greenlane</strong> </a>have invested heavily into the equipment and possess the necessary technical expertise, to offer ADAS calibration services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"ADAS Circle Of Safety\" src=\"photos/shares/ADAS-Car-Infographic-100x519-No-Text.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">More info about ADAS calibration</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>ADAS (Advanced Driver Assistance Systems) calibration refers to the process of adjusting and calibrating the sensors and cameras in a vehicle&#39;s ADAS system to ensure that it is functioning properly and accurately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Calibration is necessary to ensure that the ADAS system is working correctly and providing accurate information to the onboard computer. This is particularly important after any work is done on the vehicle that might affect the ADAS system, such as windshield replacement or suspension repairs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s important to have ADAS calibration performed by a qualified professional who is trained and equipped to perform the necessary adjustments and tests. Failure to properly calibrate the ADAS system can result in inaccurate readings and potentially dangerous driving situations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">The calibration process</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>1-All vehicles undergo a complete diagnostic scan prior to any calibrations. This scan identifies any existing or nonrelated fault codes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2-If required, the vehicle then has a full 4-wheel alignment check. The equipment used can also identify any chassis misalignment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3-Once satisfied the vehicle is aligned, the calibration process can be undertaken. Multiple radars, lidars and cameras may require calibration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4-The vehicle is road tested to check for nonconformity and to ensure ADAS systems are operational.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5-Upon return from test drive the vehicle then has a final diagnostic check to ensure no fault codes have activated during road test.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6-A comprehensive report is supplied for each vehicle along with a certificate of calibration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b style=\"text-align: center;\">Book you ADAS Calibration Service today with <a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: #2ecc71;\" href=\"#\">Autoworld Greenlane</a>.</b></p>\r\n</div>', 'image11.jpg'),
(12, 'Fleet Servicing', 'Fleet-Services-514x416.png', 'Fleet Servicing', '<div class=\"sd-left\">\r\n    <h1 style=\"color: #2ecc71 ;\">Fleet Servicing</h1>\r\n    <p>Introducing Fleet Servicing &amp; Scheduled Maintenance for Company Fleets of any size throughout New Zealand.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Nationwide Network</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span>Our national network of service centres ensures that your fleet will be reliabl</span>y<span> and conveniently serviced - New Zealand wide. More than 45 years ago, Autoworld began building a business based on service, quality and reliability.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span>Today, with over 40&nbsp;service centres nationwide - there is one near you.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Vehicle Servicing</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span>We provide an extensive range of vehicle related services including: scheduled maintenance, diagnostics, WOF inspections, tyre replacement, exhaust &amp; emission repair, brake servicing, suspension &amp; driveline component servicing &amp; replacement.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Qualified Technicians</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span>Top people delivering excellent service coupled with the use of quality products ensures you&rsquo;ll receive the best care for you and your vehicle fleet.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Online Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span>Autoworld partners with an organisation that specialises in fleet management administration services. The use of their programme will allow your fleet manager to monitor all aspects of your fleet expenses in a convenient way. We offer centralised billing to make it easy for you to manage payments and offer fixed vehicle servicing pricing that can reduce your overall per vehicle maintenance costs.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Contact Us</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span>Please call us directly on <a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: #2ecc71;\" href=\"#\">0800 748 786</a> or complete the contact form. We will help to determine what your specific needs are to help minimise your Fleet Servicing costs and keep your fleet moving.</span></p>\r\n</div>', 'image12.jpg'),
(13, 'Car Repairs', 'ProductCarRepairs.jpg', 'Book Your Service Today', '<div class=\"sd-left\">\r\n    <h1 style=\"color: #2ecc71 ;\">Car Repairs</h1>\r\n    <p> <span>Come to Autoworld for your car repairs and routine car maintenance work and benefit from over 45 years of vehicle repair experience and the great Autoworld service!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>If you are looking for the highest quality car repairs and vehicle maintenance work at highly competitive prices, Autoworld is the right place for you&hellip; so book in at your nearest Autoworld or make a car repair or maintenance booking online today.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>Autoworld&#39;s comprehensive vehicle repair services will be conducted by a qualified Autoworld vehicle technician and we&rsquo;ll cover the engine, braking systems, shock absorbers, exhaust systems and lubricant system to name but a few. Check out our car maintenance schedule below to see when your vehicle is due for maintenance or book your vehicle in online.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">How Often Should My Vehicle System be Inspected or Checked?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> <span>Braking Systems Every 15,000 km</span></li>\r\n<li> <span>Every twelve months</span></li>\r\n<li> <span>Shock Absorbers Every 25,000 km</span></li>\r\n<li> <span>Exhaust Systems Every 20,000 km</span></li>\r\n<li> <span>Electrical Systems (vehicle computer ECU) Every 15,000 km</span></li>\r\n<li> <span>Lubrication Systems Every 15,000 km</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>Autoworld also carry out a range of detailed vehicle system checks, preventative car maintenance inspections to help you protect your vehicle and ensure that you are getting the most from it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Engine Performance</h3>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>Despite the misconception that many newer vehicles no longer require regular maintenance, all vehicles require routine maintenance in order to avoid performance problems such as hard starting, misfiring, surging, hesitation, and stalling. Not only does engine maintenance reduce the chance of expensive car repairs further down the line, a proper service will also save you money by reducing fuel consumption.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>At Autoworld, we have developed an in-depth list of services you should have regularly performed along with any of the vehicle&#39;s manufacturer&#39;s scheduled maintenance.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Spark Plugs</h3>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>Damaged or worn-out spark plugs can cause drivability problems and decrease fuel efficiency. Depending on the type of spark plugs your vehicle uses, you should replace your spark plugs every 50,000 to 100,000 kms to maximise power, performance, and fuel economy.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Spark Plugs Wires and Coils</h3>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>Extreme under-hood temperatures, voltage spikes, debris, or corrosion can damage plug wires and coils leading to costly and unwanted car repairs later on. Have your spark plug wires and coils inspected by a Autoworld car mechanic or technician when you replace your spark plugs.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Cambelt Replacement</h3>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>You must replace your car&#39;s cambelt to avoid expensive car repairs and possible engine failure. Please advise make, model and year, along with mileage and we will tell you when this must be changed</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Water Pump</h3>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>In most cases this component is driven by the cambelt and usually requires replacing at the same interval to avoid another costly bill.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Clutch Replacement</h3>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>Lack of drive or crunching gears means your clutch needs attention, bring it in for a quick simple test drive, it maybe just an adjustment, otherwise we can replace the clutch and get you back on the road.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Air Filter</h3>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>A dirty air filter blocks airflow to your vehicle&#39;s engine and makes it work harder, causing a decline in horsepower and fuel economy. The air filter should be inspected with every oil change. It is not uncommon, under certain driving conditions, for the air filter to be replaced frequently.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Fuel Filter</h3>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>The fuel filter, PCV valve and breather element are often neglected during a routine service, which can lead to a number of drivability problems. Change them every two years or 30,000 kms to ensure proper vehicle performance and fuel efficiency.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">Fuel Injection System Cleaner</h3>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>Rough idle, engine hesitation and declining fuel economy are often due to fuel system deposits. Adding a fuel system cleaner to your gas tank regularly, removes deposits and restores engine performance and fuel economy.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #3498db  ;\">General Car Repairs</h3>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>A qualified Autoworld car mechanic or technician has the expertise to diagnose and repair most engine related faults e.g. overheating related issues. Our team of qualified car mechanics and technicians will ensure your vehicle is repaired to the highest standard to get you back on the road with minimum delay.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p> <span>Don&#39;t forget, we have various car repair and car maintenance packages where we&#39;ll inspect all of the above components and give you a thoroughly written estimate for whatever work needs to be performed. Autoworld is and will always be your one stop for complete car care, so get in touch with us when you need vehicle repair services from one of NZ&rsquo;s leading automotive repair companies.</span></p>\r\n</div>', 'servicegirl.jpg');

